entries.title: 12 people injured in shooting at Louisiana nightclub
entries.description: Authorities say 12 people were injured in a shooting at a nightclub in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, early Sunday

entries.title: Kansas man arrested after house fire killed woman, 2 girls
entries.description: The only survivor of a Kansas house fire that killed a woman and two young girls has been arrested on suspicion of setting the blaze

entries.title: Ryanair flight lands safely in Athens after bomb scare
entries.description: A scheduled flight from Katowice, Poland, has arrived safely at Athens International Airport after an alert was issued about a possible bomb onboard

entries.title: Lawmakers seek to bar insurrectionists from holding office
entries.description: Democratic lawmakers in a handful of states are trying to send a message two years after the violent attack on the U.S. Capitol

entries.title: Washington county mistakenly releases 460,000 partial SSNs
entries.description: A Washington county inadvertently released nearly half a million partial Social Security Numbers when responding to a routine public records request in December, according to county officials

entries.title: Huge waves bring Hawaii surf contest The Eddie after hiatus
entries.description: One of the world’s most prestigious and storied surfing contests went forward in Hawaii for the first time in seven years

entries.title: France, Germany renew alliance strained amid war in Ukraine
entries.description: France and Germany have commemorated the 60th anniversary of their post-World War II friendship treaty by committing to “unwavering support” for Ukraine and to strengthening the European Union

entries.title: Report: Man loses testicle after clubbing by Paris police
entries.description: A French newspaper reports that doctors amputated the testicle of a young man who got clubbed in the groin by a police officer during a huge Paris demonstration

entries.title: Storm system threatening Northeast with heavy snow, rain
entries.description: A massive storm system that brought nearly a foot of snow to some parts of the Midwest is now threatening the Northeast with heavy snow, torrential rain and high winds.

entries.title: Sanders' Latinx ban wades into community's generational rift
entries.description: Arkansas Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders is tapping into a debate that's sharply divided Latinos with her decision to ban most state agencies from using the gender neutral term Latinx

entries.title: Israel's Netanyahu fires Cabinet ally, heeding court ruling
entries.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has fired a key Cabinet ally, heeding a Supreme Court ruling commanding him to do so and deepening a rift over the power of the courts

entries.title: What would have been 50th anniversary of Roe v. Wade sees protests, celebration
entries.description: Sunday marks what would have been the 50th anniversary of Roe v. Wade and is being commemorated by protests and celebrations of the fight for abortion rights.

entries.title: Multiple dead in shooting in Monterey Park, California
entries.description: Multiple people were shot late Saturday in Monterey Park, California, a city hosting a Lunar New Year festival this weekend.

entries.title: US ambassador heading to Africa as part of Biden's big push
entries.description: The U.S. ambassador to the United Nations is the second Cabinet member heading to Africa as part of President Joe Biden’s big push to engage with the world’s second-largest continent

entries.title: Building collapse in Syrian city of Aleppo leaves 10 dead
entries.description: Syrian state media says a building has collapsed in a neighborhood in the northern city of Aleppo, killing at least 10 people, including one child

entries.title: WATCH:  Ice crystals form pattern on freezing bubble
entries.description: Video shows ice crystals forming on a freezing soap bubble in Reno, Nevada, as the region experiences cold temperatures.

entries.title: 6 arrested in Atlanta protests over proposed police training facility
entries.description: A protest erupted Saturday night in Atlanta over a proposed police training facility.

entries.title: NYC to use cruise ship terminal as asylum-seeker shelter
entries.description: New York City is temporarily turning a cruise ship terminal into a shelter and services hub for asylum-seekers

entries.title: Bitter cold continues in Southwest into next week, NV to NM
entries.description: Unusually cold weather is expected to continue across most of the Southwest.

entries.title: Peru closes Machu Picchu as anti-government protests grow
entries.description: Peru has indefinitely shut its iconic tourist site Machu Picchu.

entries.title: Biden's home searched by Justice Department, more classified material found
entries.description: The search lasted roughly 12 hours, beginning at 9:45 a.m. and ending around 10:30 p.m., according to Biden's personal attorney Bob Bauer.

entries.title: Time's Up to halt operations, shift resources to legal fund
entries.description: The #MeToo-era organization is ceasing operations, at least in its current form.
